    "body": "miri.py will stop with NoneType errors, because the script doesn't handle the fresh build yet.\n```py\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"miri.py\", line 83, in <lambda>\n    gdb.post_event(lambda: self.exit_to_another_inferior())\n                           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^\n  File \"miri.py\", line 92, in exit_to_another_inferior\n    elif (val := self.miri_inferior()):\n                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^\n  File \"miri.py\", line 146, in miri_inferior\n    if status.cmdline.is_cargo_miri():\n       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'is_cargo_miri'\n```\n\nTo run miri.py, run `OSDK_LOCAL_DEV=1 cargo osdk miri test` first to fully build the code with miri, and then run `OSDK_LOCAL_DEV=1 rust-gdb -x miri.gdb --args cargo osdk miri test` to reach desired breakpoints in miri source code.",
